# Analytics, Consent & Onboarding

## PostHog Analytics
```javascript
// Track custom events
Analytics.track('custom_event', { property: 'value' });
Analytics.trackFeature('api_key_setup', 'clicked');

// User identification (automatic on login)
Analytics.identify(userId, { email });

// Workflow events (automatic)
Analytics.trackWorkflowStarted({ inputMethod: 'url' });
Analytics.trackWorkflowCompleted({ matchScore: 0.85 });
```
Analytics only fires if the user has accepted analytics cookies. Events queue until consent is given.

## Cookie Consent
```javascript
// Check before storing non-essential data
CookieConsent.hasConsent();  // true/false — accepts analytics cookies

// Get full preferences
CookieConsent.getPreferences();
// { essential: true, functional: false, analytics: false }

// Programmatic consent
CookieConsent.acceptAll();
CookieConsent.rejectAll();
CookieConsent.savePreferences({ functional: true, analytics: true });
```

Cookie types:
| Type | Required | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| Essential | Always | Auth, session, security tokens |
| Functional | Optional | User preferences, UI state |
| Analytics | Optional | PostHog event tracking |

## Onboarding Tour
```javascript
Onboarding.start();    // start tour
Onboarding.reset();    // reset + show again
Onboarding.skip();     // skip tour
```

Tour auto-shows on first dashboard visit when `localStorage.onboarding_completed` is missing.

**Returning users:** if the key is missing but `GET /api/v1/applications/stats/overview` shows `total_applications > 0`, onboarding auto-completes silently (tour state is browser-local only — without this, clearing storage or switching browsers re-shows the tour).

**Tour steps (conditional):**
- Welcome *(always)*
- Install Chrome Extension *(always)* — explains load-unpacked dev flow
- Set Up Your API Key *(only when `needsApiKey` — server has no key AND no Vertex AI)*
- Analyze Job Postings *(always)*
- Career Tools *(always — last step, "Next" becomes "Get Started ✓")*

**`needsApiKey` condition** is evaluated by `checkServerApiKey()` which calls `GET /api/v1/profile/api-key/status` directly via `fetch()` with the user's auth token from `localStorage`. It returns `true` (key available, skip step) when `has_user_key || server_has_key || use_vertex_ai`. The old implementation used `window.app.apiCall()` which is `undefined` on dashboard pages — always use direct `fetch()`.

**CSS lives in `ui/dashboard/index.html`** inside the nonce-gated `<style nonce="...">` block — **never inject `<style>` from `onboarding.js`**. Dynamically created `<style>` elements cannot carry a server-issued nonce and are silently blocked by the CSP `style-src` policy.

## Cookie Consent — CSS Location

All cookie banner and preferences modal CSS lives in **`ui/static/css/app.css`** under the `/* ── Cookie Consent Banner ── */` section.

`cookie-consent.js`'s `_addStyles()` method is intentionally emptied — it returns immediately without injecting anything. The old `document.createElement('style')` approach was blocked by CSP.

**Never re-add dynamic style injection to `cookie-consent.js`.**

CSS class reference for cookie banner:
- `#cookie-consent-banner` — fixed bottom bar, slides up via `.visible` class
- `.cookie-consent-content` — flex layout, max-width 1200px
- `.cookie-btn`, `.cookie-btn-accept`, `.cookie-btn-reject`, `.cookie-btn-secondary` — button variants
- `#cookie-preferences-modal` — full-screen backdrop modal for cookie categories
- `.cookie-modal-content`, `.cookie-modal-header`, `.cookie-modal-body`, `.cookie-modal-footer` — modal structure
- `.cookie-category`, `.cookie-category-name`, `.cookie-required`, `.cookie-category-desc` — preference rows

**"Tour" button in Settings → Privacy** calls `restartOnboarding()` which clears `localStorage` and immediately redirects to `/dashboard` — no intermediate banner. The tour fires automatically on arrival.

